{"word":"H6049 - עָנַן - ʻânan - aw-nan' - [idiom] bring","slug":"H6049","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עָנַן</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻânan"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-nan'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>[idiom] bring"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E2;&#x05E0;&#x05DF; - &#x201B;a&#x0302;nan</b> - <i>aw-nan'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>cover</i>; used only as denominative from <a href=\"#/H6051\">H6051</a>, to <i>cloud</i> over; figuratively to <i>act covertly</i>, that is, practise magic: -  X bring, enchanter, Meonemin, observe (-r of) times, soothsayer, sorcerer."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6052\">H6052</a>, <a href=\"#/H6054\">H6054</a>, <a href=\"#/H6055\">H6055</a>"}]}